remarks: If ` ps ` holds when ` ph ` occurs as well as when ` ph ` does not occur, then ` ps ` holds.  If ` ps ` or ` ph ` occurs and if the occurences of ` ph ` has ` ps ` as a necessary consequence, then ` ps ` takes place. Identical to ~ pm2.6 .  Proposition 46 of [Frege1879] p. 48.
